<item>
            <title>[CXF-1749] Quick Fix for JMS Encoding issue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1749</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The encoding of JMS Messages is wrong if they are sent as TextMessage and the platform encoding is not equal to the message encoding. This issue is linked to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1668&quot; title=&quot;Wrong encoding using JMS Transport&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-1668&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-1668&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. While the other issue handles a long term solution like proposed from Daniel Kulp this issue aims to provide a short term fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The short term fix is to avoid the simple getBytes() call and instead call getBytes(&amp;lt;encoding&amp;gt;) with the correct encoding.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
