                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12622690" author="chris@die-schneider.net" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 20:55:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Link to longer problem description, discussion and the proposal for a long term solution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622697" author="chris@die-schneider.net" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 21:01:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the short term fix we have to find out which encoding the message uses. Is it safe to read this encoding from the &amp;lt;?xml encoding=&quot;&quot;?&amp;gt; ?  Or is the encoding always UTF-8?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643773" author="njiang" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2008 07:43:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we can leverage the content-type which holds the charset (encoding) information. &lt;br/&gt;
If there is no charset information you use the default encoding UTF-8, otherwise we set the message encoding to the charset.&lt;br/&gt;
BTW, there is Message.ENCODING  key in the Message , I think we need to use it to specify the text message&apos;s encoding.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
